The paper proposes a novel learning-based hashing method for image retrieval, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The method involves linear regression and boosting, which are common techniques in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. The paper also mentions information retrieval and similarity search, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that has not been used before, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
